“It’s not a Scandinavian scarf. It’s an Indian dupatta.”
Recently, a global fashion house mistook a dupatta - rich with handwoven heritage - for a mere scarf. But we’re here to remind the world: this isn’t just fabric. It’s karigari. It’s identity. It’s history carried on shoulders, pleated with pride.
From the intricate zari of Banaras to the delicate phulkari of Punjab, every thread tells a story - not of trend, but of tradition.
Fashion is global now. But credit should be too.
Let’s not just wear the culture. Let’s acknowledge it.
Indian craftsmanship isn’t a trend. It’s timeless.

#induancraftsmanship  #dupatta  #induancouture  #versatiledupatta  #fashioncreator  #fashionnerd  #fashioncontentcreator

latestPosts.caption:
“Let’s talk glow-up in a bottle!
If you haven’t tried The Ordinary AHA 30% + BHA 2% Peeling Solution yet… girl, you’re seriously missing out. This weekly reset for your skin is my go-to for when my face feels dull, textured, or just blah.

It’s packed with alpha hydroxy acids (AHA) to exfoliate the skin’s surface and beta hydroxy acid (BHA) to clear out pores deep down—think smoother texture, brighter tone, and fewer breakouts. Plus, it helps fade acne scars and gives you that post-facial glow without the spa price tag.

Use it once a week for 10 mins, and don’t forget sunscreen the next day—trust me, your skin will thank you.

Skincare doesn’t have to be complicated—sometimes it’s just one power step away.”

🧴- @theordinary
